ics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada's Camryn Rogers (76.97 meters) got the gold, but it was still a historic day for the 2018 grad.\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 350, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9983475702349387, \"rank\": 0.0016517957310533652, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 359, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Camryn_Rogers\", \"score\": 0.9999999840470083, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Camryn Rogers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Camryn_Rogers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Camryn_Rogers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a great Olympic arc after Echikunwoke missed the Tokyo 2020 games (played in 2021) due to lack of adequate drug testing.\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 508, \"end\": 513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999954323224938, \"rank\": 4.567680695068119e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasno fault of her ownafter originally committing to compete for Nigeria.\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 648, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.8882762504746968, \"rank\": 0.12518698361910863, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their athletic federation did not send her requested testers after she asked multiple times and she could not compete as a result.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, she's made history for the United States.\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.968508794937601, \"rank\": 0.031105877137706368, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to WLWT's Charlie Clifford, she is the third UC track and field athlete to win a medal.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WLWT\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"WLWT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WLWT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WLWT\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Kingdon_Clifford\", \"score\": 0.9259139603557116, \"rank\": 0.08001395369836152, \"text\": \"Clifford\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Kingdon_Clifford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Kingdon_Clifford\"}, {\"begin\": 891, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Urban_contemporary_music\", \"score\": 0.9542747275987944, \"rank\": 0.0477560577971094, \"text\": \"UC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Urban_contemporary_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Urban_contemporary_music\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Annette Echikunwoke throws a season-best 75.48m to bring home a SILVER MEDAL for Team USA!\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Annette_Echikunwoke\",